HEADWORD: oedema
<hw>oe*de"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<?/ a swelling, tumor, fr. <?/ to swell.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
swelling from effusion of watery fluid in the cellular tissue beneath
the skin or mucous membranes; dropsy of the subcutaneous cellular
tissue.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>edema</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oedematous</ent>⟦br⟧
